This is a quick overview of an app functionality:

Login Screen is loaded initially allowing user to register or sign in using Firebase =>

After Login/Sign Up ContactList screen is loaded. Header has SignOut Icon to return to Login.

Bottom navigation has 3 additional screens to load and is available from each of them.

ContactList has a List of contacts loaded from Firebase. On top there's a button to open
Dialog with input fields to create new contact. Contacts are sorted alphabetically and have
a Delete button on their right.

Phone screen has an API to chose country code, Input field to complete number, and button to
open device's native phone app with prefilled number.

Message screen allows user to chose a reciever and write a message. Those will be transfered
to phone native app by click on Send Sms button.